[3]
From: ProMEDmail
Date: Tuesday, October 30, 2001; 1:00 PM
Source: Washington Post 29 Oct 2001 [edited]
<http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A5787-2001Oct29.html>
List of Anthrax Cases, Locations [as of 29 Oct 2001]
--------------------------------------------
Deaths from inhalation anthrax:
* (male) 63, photo editor, the Sun, American Media Inc., Boca Raton,
Fla.
Died Oct. 5.
* (male) 55, Washington postal worker. Died Oct. 21.
* (male) 47, Washington postal worker. Died Oct. 22.
Contracted inhalation anthrax:
* (female) 61, Bronx, New York, works at Manhattan, Eye, Ear and
Throat Hospital.
* (male) 73, mail room worker at AMI in Boca Raton.
* 59-year-old mail handler from State Department offsite mail room.
* (male) 57, Washington postal worker.
- Unnamed Washington postal worker.
- Unnamed New Jersey postal worker
Contracted skin anthrax:
* (female) 51, works near the Hamilton Township, New Jersey,
mail-processing building that handled anthrax letters mailed to Sen.
Tom Daschle (D-S.D.) and NBC anchorman Tom Brokaw
* (female) 38, assistant to NBC anchorman Tom Brokaw, New York.
(Another NBC aide has "suspicious and probable" case.)
* (male) 7 months, infant son of ABC News producer, New York.
* (female) 27, assistant to CBS anchorman Dan Rather, New York.
* (female) 30, assistant to editorial page editor at New York Post.
* (female), letter carrier at West Trenton post office in Ewing, N.J.
* (male) 35, sorts and loads mail in Hamilton, N.J.
Anthrax found at: (partial list)
* Friendship Post Office in Northwest Washington.
* Offsite facility that processes mail for the Justice Department.
* Offsite warehouse that processes mail for the Supreme Court. as well
as the mailroom of the court building.
* Buildings used by the Department of Health & Human Services and the
Food & Drug Administration
* Offsite mail-screening facility for White House on military
installation.
* Mail processing building of the CIA in McLean, Va.
* State Department offsite mail facility in Sterling, Va. as well as
the main building.
* Mailroom in the Walter Reed Army Institute of Research in Silver
Spring, Maryland.
* Brentwood postal facility in Northeast Washington.
* A post office in Southwest Washington.
* Senate Majority Leader Tom Daschle's Washington office in the Hart
Senate Office Building, on letter postmarked Oct. 9, Trenton, N.J.
* Stairway between the Hart building's eighth and ninth floors, a
ninth-floor ventilation filter and in the area immediately in front of
a first floor freight elevator.
* Dirksen Senate Office Building, where mail for Senate offices is
processed; Ford House Office Building, where mail for House offices is
processed; offices of three members of Congress in the Longworth House
Office Building; and an offsite postal facility where all
congressional mail is processed.
* NBC, New York, on letter postmarked Sept. 18, Trenton, N.J.
* New York Post, on letter postmarked Sept. 18, Trenton, N.J.
* CBS, Rather's office and anteroom.
* US Postal Service's Morgan Processing and Distribution Center, New
York.
* Regional mail center, Hamilton, N.J.
* Princeton, N.J. post office.
* American Media Inc., Boca Raton, Fla., on keyboard of man who died
and in mail room.
* Three U.S. Postal Service facilities in Florida (two in Boca Raton,
where AMI is based; one in Lake Worth, near AMI's former address in
Lantana).
* Manhattan office of New York Gov. George Pataki.
